                        <head>466. Editorial Note</head>
                        <p>On April 2, President <persName corresp="#p_EMS1">Eisenhower</persName>
                            approved <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5809, “U.S. Policy in
                            Mainland Southeast Asia,” which superseded <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 5612/1, September 5, 1956. For text, see <ref target="frus1955-57v21#pg_252"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                    Relations</hi>, 1955–1957, volume XXI, pages 252</ref>–<ref target="frus1955-57v21#pg_263">263</ref>.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>